罗斯维尔办公室怎么说？
What'd their office in Rossville have to say?

174
00:16:57,260 --> 00:17:01,890
他们证实那些男孩回到这里向会众道歉
They confirmed that the boys came back here to apologize to the congregation.

175
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,540
对不起 你们没有表决权
Sorry you folks didn't get to vote.

176
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:07,900
我想大家从来不知道你们甚至有权
I suppose most of you never knew you even had one.

177
00:17:08,270 --> 00:17:10,900
现在 你们没有地方做礼拜了
Now you got no place to go on Sunday.

178
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:16,950
显然 他们回到这之后 与沿途的居民有交谈
Apparently, after they came back here, they talked to some locals down the road.

179
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,520
我们应该从这里入手
I think that's where we should start.

180
00:17:18,620 --> 00:17:22,190
嗯 你可以问问你他们 但他们不会说的
Well, you can talk to them, but they won't talk to you.

181
00:17:22,490 --> 00:17:25,770
我们走后 这些人还得在这里生活
These people have to live here long after we're packed up and gone.

182
00:17:25,870 --> 00:17:27,790
他们宁愿忍住不说 也不会告诉我们
They'd rather bite their tongue off than talk to us.

183
00:17:28,540 --> 00:17:30,380
按局程序 安德森先生
Bureau procedure, Mr. Anderson.

184
00:17:38,260 --> 00:17:42,060
教堂着火 而你跑回家 是这样吗？
The church caught fire and you ran home, is that correct?

185
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:44,020
是的
Yes, sir.

186
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:46,960
四个白人阻止你？
And then the four white men stopped you?

187
00:17:47,060 --> 00:17:48,390
是的
Yes, sir.

188
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:51,150
这四个白人打你丈夫？
And these four white men attacked your husband?

189
00:17:52,110 --> 00:17:53,860
是的
Yes, sir.

190
00:17:54,570 --> 00:17:56,990
你不认识他们
But you can't identify them?

191
00:17:58,820 --> 00:18:00,450
不认识
No, sir.

192
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:03,850
你把这报告给警察了吗？
Did you report this to the police?

193
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:05,910
没有
No, sir.

194
00:18:06,580 --> 00:18:08,980
但你告诉民权男孩发生了什么？
But you told the civil rights boys what happened?

195
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:10,670
是的
Yes, sir.

196
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:16,130
夫人 他们说了要去那里吗？
Madam, did they tell you where they were going after that?

197
00:18:19,340 --> 00:18:20,550
没有
No, sir.

198
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:22,580
什么也没有说？
Nothing?

199
00:18:22,680 --> 00:18:24,680
没有
No, sir.

200
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,940
好的 谢谢 夫人
All right. Thank you, Madam.

201
00:18:29,140 --> 00:18:31,020
别客气
You're welcome.

202
00:18:43,780 --> 00:18:45,330
快点
Come on, boy.

203
00:18:45,540 --> 00:18:46,830
开门
Open up.

204
00:18:48,790 --> 00:18:49,940
你哥哥霍利斯在吗？
Your brother Hollis here?

205
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:51,120
在
Yes, sir.

206
00:18:51,330 --> 00:18:53,710
叫他起来 我们要见他
Well, wake his ass up. We want to see him.

207
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,670
- 为什么？ - 叫他起来
- Why?  - Just wake him up, boy.

208
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:56,950
怎么了？发什么了什么？
Why? What's the matter?

209
00:18:57,050 --> 00:18:58,380
你在呀
There you are!

210
00:19:01,180 --> 00:19:02,760
来这里
Come here, boy!

211
00:19:03,220 --> 00:19:04,330
霍利斯
Hollis!

212
00:19:06,060 --> 00:19:08,390
回来 他妈的黑鬼
Get your ass back here, you fucking nigger!

213
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:11,270
霍利斯 霍利斯
Hollis! Hollis!

214
00:19:17,820 --> 00:19:19,110
混蛋
Shit!

215
00:19:26,620 --> 00:19:29,110
最好别让我们看到你和FBI说话
We better not catch you talking to the FBI.

216
00:19:29,380 --> 00:19:31,660
否则你死定了
You'll be dead, boy.

217
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:52,350
你同情这些孩子？
You admire these kids, don't you?

218
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:54,770
你不吗？
Don't you?

219
00:19:56,190 --> 00:19:58,520
我想他们是被利用了
I think they're being used.

220
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:02,780
他们被大众车送到这里 一群混蛋
I think they're being sent down here in their Volkswagens and their sneakers,

221
00:20:02,950 --> 00:20:04,740
打爆了他们的头
just to get their heads cracked open.

222
00:20:04,950 --> 00:20:08,330
你可曾想到或许他们坚信他们做的？
Did it ever occur to you that maybe they believed in what they were doing?

223
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:10,600
他们想过最终会死吗？
Did it ever occur to them they were gonna end up dead?

224
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:12,000
也许吧
Maybe.

225
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:15,790
在华盛顿 他们肯定就知道
In Washington they sure as hell knew, didn't they?

226
00:20:16,540 --> 00:20:18,170
有一些事值得为之去死
Some things are worth dying for.

227
00:20:21,130 --> 00:20:24,300
这里的人们领会有点不同
Down here they see things a little differently.

228
00:20:26,050 --> 00:20:28,720
他们认为值得为一些事去杀人
People down here feel some things are worth killing for.

229
00:20:32,850 --> 00:20:36,440
这一切仇视从何而来？
Where does it come from, all this hatred?

230
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,820
你知道 我还是小孩时
You know, when I was a little boy,

231
00:20:42,030 --> 00:20:45,280
一个名叫门罗的黑人老农住在我们街的另一头
an old Negro farmer lived down the road, name of Monroe.

232
00:20:46,410 --> 00:20:47,660
他是…
And he was...

233
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:52,580
我想他只比我父亲运气好一点
I guess he was a little luckier than my daddy was.

234
00:20:56,540 --> 00:20:58,670
他买了一头骡子
He bought himself a mule.

235
00:21:00,210 --> 00:21:03,170
这是那个镇周围的一笔大交易
That was a big deal around that town.

236
00:21:03,630 --> 00:21:06,130
我父亲讨厌那头骡子
My daddy hated that mule.

237
00:21:06,340 --> 00:21:08,450
因为他的朋友骗他说
Because his friends were always kidding him about

238
00:21:08,550 --> 00:21:11,680
看到门罗用骡子耕地
how they saw Monroe plowing with his new mule.

239
00:21:11,850 --> 00:21:16,940
既然有一头骡子 门罗打算租另一块地
And Monroe was gonna rent another field now that he had a mule.

240
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:21,690
一天早上骡子死了
One morning that mule just showed up dead.

241
00:21:23,780 --> 00:21:26,150
他们在水里下毒
They poisoned the water.

242
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:30,410
打那之后 我父亲再没提过那头骡子
And after that, there was never any mention about that mule around my daddy.

243
00:21:30,620 --> 00:21:32,700
从来没再提过
Just never came up.

244
00:21:35,910 --> 00:21:37,700
一次我们沿街开车
So one time, we were driving down the road,

245
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:40,540
经过门罗的地方 那里空荡荡的
and we passed Monroe's place and we saw it was empty.

246
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:44,050
我想他刚收拾行李离开了吧 去北边或其他地方
He just packed and left. I guess gone up north or something.

247
00:21:46,510 --> 00:21:50,390
我一看父亲的脸
I looked over at my daddy's face

248
00:21:51,470 --> 00:21:54,100
就知道是他干的
and I knew he'd done it.

249
00:21:54,310 --> 00:21:58,560
他也清楚我知道 他很羞愧
He saw that I knew. He was ashamed.

250
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:02,020
我想他很羞愧
I guess he was ashamed.

251
00:22:04,070 --> 00:22:05,900
他看着我说
He looked at me and he said,

252
00:22:06,740 --> 00:22:09,570
“儿子 要是不能优于黑人 还能优于谁？”
"If you ain't any better than a nigger, son, who are you better than? "

253
00:22:13,290 --> 00:22:14,810
你认为那是理由吗？
You think that's an excuse?

254
00:22:14,910 --> 00:22:18,660
这不是理由 这只是我父亲的故事
No, it's not an excuse. It's just a story about my daddy.

255
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:25,910
为此你离开了那里？
Where's that leave you?

256
00:22:26,010 --> 00:22:28,700
如此充满憎恨的一个老人
With an old man that was just so full of hate

257
00:22:28,750 --> 00:22:33,470
他不知道那是贫穷扼杀了他
that he didn't know being poor was what was killing him.

258
00:22:41,770 --> 00:22:43,940
关掉灯 关掉灯
Get the light! Get the light!

259
00:22:45,940 --> 00:22:47,440
你没事吧？
You all right?

260
00:22:58,250 --> 00:23:00,290
他们知道我们在这里
I guess they know we're here.

261
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:39,250
现在你知道你到了什么地方
Now you know what you're getting into.

262
00:23:39,450 --> 00:23:42,000
我会与华盛顿联系 请求派更多的密探
I'm gonna call Washington. I need more agents.

263
00:23:42,620 --> 00:23:46,000
我说这是错误的做法 你会改变主意吗？
Would it make any difference if I told you that's exactly the wrong thing to do?

264
00:23:46,210 --> 00:23:47,670
不会
No.

265
00:24:35,470 --> 00:24:38,350
整个地方一个月七十五元
The whole place for 75 a month.

266
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:41,640
这是个私人场所 在镇中心 是个很好的地方
It's private, it's central, it's perfect.

267
00:24:41,850 --> 00:24:45,020
能容纳一百多个密探 或许两百个
There's room for 100 more agents. 200, maybe.

268
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,000
如果加上楼座
More on the balcony.

269
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:50,130
安德森先生 我们在找三个男孩
We're trying to find the three boys, Mr. Anderson.

270
00:24:50,230 --> 00:24:52,280
我会接受一切能得到的帮助
I'll take all the help I can get.

271
00:24:54,530 --> 00:24:55,530
这机遇何时开始的？
When's the show start?

272
00:25:50,790 --> 00:25:52,450
是谁？
Who's the big shot?

273
00:25:52,550 --> 00:25:54,050
三K党
That's the Klans.

274
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:58,680
没有尖帽子 却有许多的尖头
No pointy hats, but plenty of pointy heads.

275
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:02,220
我去查查车牌
Let me run a check on the plates.

276
00:26:32,590 --> 00:26:35,000
下午好 先生们
Good afternoon, gentlemen.

277
00:26:35,170 --> 00:26:36,460
安德森
Anderson.

278
00:26:36,670 --> 00:26:38,420
来向市长提尔曼先生问候
Won't you say hello to our mayor, Mr. Tilman, here?

279
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:40,450
你好 安德森
How do you do, Anderson?

280
00:26:40,550 --> 00:26:42,340
市长先生 理发师先生
Mr. Mayor, Mr. Barber.

281
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:45,970
看起来象一个地方
This looks like the place to be.

282
00:26:46,560 --> 00:26:48,270
即使对我来说
Even for me.

283
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:52,940
没有比理发店更舒服的地方了
Nothing like a barber shop for jawing your socks off.

284
00:26:53,730 --> 00:26:55,760
你从何处来？安德森
Where you from anyway, Anderson?

285
00:26:55,860 --> 00:26:57,400
密西西比州桑顿市
Thornton, Mississippi, sir.

286
00:26:57,690 --> 00:26:59,320
从田纳西州来只是胡说
Just a spit from Tennessee.

287
00:26:59,530 --> 00:27:03,030
你必须懂得这里的规矩
Well then you must know how we all feel down here.

288
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:06,870
我们不喜欢告诉外人我们怎样生活
We don't take to outsiders telling us how to live our lives.

289
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:09,700
我很乐意告诉你这里的黑人很快乐
And I'm here to tell you our nigras were happy,

290
00:27:09,800 --> 00:27:13,700
直到那些披头族把事情搞得沸沸扬扬
till those beatnik college kids came down here stirring things up.

291
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:15,710
在这之前没有任何人抱怨
Before that, there wasn't anybody complaining.

292
00:27:17,130 --> 00:27:18,670
没人敢吧
Nobody dared.

293
00:27:20,380 --> 00:27:23,340
这里有一个真正平安的社区 安德森
We got a real peaceful community down here, Anderson.

294
00:27:23,550 --> 00:27:28,390
他们就象其他民族 你要是逼得过分…
Of course they're just like any other folks, I reckon, and push them too far...

295
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:33,310
我估计会象三捆旧炸药
The way I figure it, it's like three sticks of old dynamite.

296
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:38,530
要是触发了 就得上街收尸
You shake it up, and we're gonna be scraping bodies off the street.

297
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:43,610
我只是来调查三个失踪的孩子 问一些问题
I'm just down here to investigate the missing three kids, ask some questions.

298
00:27:43,820 --> 00:27:45,900
即使全部归结起来是肉汁
If this all boiled down to gravy,

299
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:48,950
也盖不住鸡油煎牛排
there wouldn't be enough to cover up a chicken-fried steak.

300
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:53,620
你要找的孩子？我敢跟你打赌
Them kids you're looking for? I'll just about bet you a shiny new dime

301
00:27:53,830 --> 00:27:56,490
他们一定在芝加哥
they're sitting up in Chicago right now

302
00:27:56,590 --> 00:27:59,160
喝着冰啤酒 笑着谈论
drinking a cold beer and having a big laugh

303
00:27:59,260 --> 00:28:01,400
在这里引起的混乱
about all the commotion they've stirred up down here.

304
00:28:01,470 --> 00:28:02,880
我当然希望如此
Well, I sure hope so.

305
00:28:03,760 --> 00:28:05,720
你可以告诉你上司
You tell your bosses

306
00:28:05,930 --> 00:28:09,260
人们有对南方的偏见
people got the wrong idea about the South.

307
00:28:09,430 --> 00:28:11,600
你知道我指的是什么
You know what I'm talking about.

308
00:28:11,810 --> 00:28:15,310
人人衣着褴褛 落后 文盲
Everybody running around ragged, backwards, illiterate,

309
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:19,270
一日三餐腌猪肉和玉米饼
eating sow-belly and corn pone three times a day.

310
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:23,450
安德森 简单的事实是我们有两种文明
Simple fact is, Anderson, we got two cultures down here.

311
00:28:23,610 --> 00:28:27,200
白种人文明和有色人种文明
White culture, and the colored culture.

312
00:28:27,410 --> 00:28:29,560
这一直存在
That's the way it always has been.

313
00:28:29,660 --> 00:28:31,790
并且会永远存在
That's the way it always will be.

314
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:34,070
美国其他地方看不到
Rest of America don't see it that way, Mr. Mayor.

315
00:28:34,170 --> 00:28:36,460
美国其他地方屁都没有
Rest of America don't mean jack shit.

316
00:28:36,670 --> 00:28:38,880
你在密西西比州
You in Mississippi now.

317
00:28:39,550 --> 00:28:41,220
这是肯定的
That's for sure.

318
00:28:44,130 --> 00:28:45,700
理发师先生 比分多少？
What's the score, Mr. Barber?

319
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:47,640
圣·路易斯队领先 五比零
St. Louis on top, five to nothing.

320
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,040
哪一局？
What inning is it?

321
00:28:49,140 --> 00:28:50,390
第七局末
Bottom of the seventh.

322
00:28:50,600 --> 00:28:52,330
安德森 你喜欢棒球？
You like baseball, do you, Anderson?

323
00:28:52,430 --> 00:28:54,100
嗯 我喜欢 你知道…
Yeah, I do. You know...

324
00:28:55,770 --> 00:29:00,820
只有那时黑人在白人面前挥舞棍棒
It's the only time when a black man can wave a stick at a white man

325
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:03,360
不认为是暴乱
and not start a riot.

326
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:20,710
长官
Sir.

327
00:29:21,550 --> 00:29:25,010
我们查过了车牌 是克莱顿·汤利
We checked on the plate, sir. Clayton Townley.

328
00:29:25,220 --> 00:29:29,260
汤利 三K党白骑士团的大巫师
Townley. Grand Wizard of the White Knights of the Ku Klux Klan.

329
00:29:29,470 --> 00:29:32,220
就是他 我们有此车的线索
That's him. Oh, and I think we have a lead on the car, sir.

330
00:29:32,430 --> 00:29:34,600
旅馆的一个乔克托人知道在何处
A Choctaw on the reservation thinks he knows where it is.

331
00:29:34,810 --> 00:29:36,040
我在等一个电话
I'm waiting for a call.

332
00:29:36,140 --> 00:29:37,350
很好
Good.

333
00:29:53,370 --> 00:29:55,860
下周二有约会吗？
You have your appointment next Tuesday, right?

334
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:58,420
到时见 再见
I'll see you then. Bye-bye.

335
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,730
你要去…
You gonna go to...

336
00:30:25,030 --> 00:30:26,820
下午好 女士们
Afternoon, ladies.

337
00:30:27,860 --> 00:30:29,400
能为你效劳吗？
Can I help you?

338
00:30:29,610 --> 00:30:34,330
嗯 我告诉你 我只是… 我只是不喜欢这个发型 明白吗？
Well, yes, you can. I tell you, I just... I hate the way I look, you know?

339
00:30:34,540 --> 00:30:39,710
你认为怎么样？烫发？还是漂白？
What do you think? A permanent wave, maybe, or a bleached job or something?

340
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:42,500
这看起来不错 在这里做的吗？
Now, that looks pretty good. Did you have that done in here?

341
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:44,400
不 是在杰克逊
No! Jackson.

342
00:30:44,500 --> 00:30:45,900
假发是你唯一的指望
I think a wig's your only hope, hon.

343
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:48,530
你的脑袋不可能有更多选择
You ain't gonna be able to do much with that cue ball.

344
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:50,970
谢谢你
Thank you.

345
00:30:51,180 --> 00:30:55,220
即使你要问一些问题 这就是你所听到的一切
If you wanna ask custom questions, this is where you'll hear it all.

346
00:30:55,430 --> 00:30:57,200
事实上 我要问的是
Yeah, well, matter of fact, I do, you know.

347
00:30:57,400 --> 00:30:58,300
嗯
Yeah.

348
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:01,650
我想知道刚刚驱车过去的那位先生
I was just wondering who that gentleman was that just drove in over there.

349
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:03,630
我知道那不是约翰逊总统
Now, I know that isn't President Johnson.

350
00:31:03,730 --> 00:31:06,190
他是汤利 克莱顿·汤利
He's name is Townley, Clayton Townley.

351
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,260
你是FBI？
Are you one of them FBI gentlemen?

352
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:10,150
是的 夫人
Yes, Madam, I am.

353
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:13,520
那两个孩子要是死了 真令人惋惜
Well if you ask me, I think it's a shame those two kids are dead,

354
00:31:13,620 --> 00:31:15,580
希望你找到他们
but I sure hope you find them.

355
00:31:15,790 --> 00:31:19,830
谢谢 其实有三个孩子失踪 还有一个是黑人
Thank you. Actually, it's three kids that are missing. There is a colored kid also.

356
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:24,790
是否没有两个白人 你们就不会来？
Do you honestly think you people'd be down here at all, if it weren't for those two white boys?

357
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:26,750
- 也许不是 小姐  - 是夫人
- Maybe not, Miss  - Mrs.

358
00:31:27,130 --> 00:31:30,260
她丈夫是佩尔 雷·斯塔基的副警长
Pell. Her old man's Ray Stuckey's deputy.

359
00:31:33,550 --> 00:31:35,460
我单身
But I'm single.

360
00:31:38,140 --> 00:31:39,980
快看 他们来了
Look out! Here they come!

361
00:31:49,700 --> 00:31:50,700
霍利斯？
Hollis?

362
00:31:54,990 --> 00:31:57,030
退后 让开
Get back. Move out of the way.

363
00:32:01,330 --> 00:32:03,540
我们会照料 这是地方问题
We'll take care of this. It's a local problem.

364
00:32:03,750 --> 00:32:07,000
我们会处理 不需要你们帮忙
We'll handle this! We don't need your damn help!

365
00:32:09,420 --> 00:32:14,680
大街上有血不太好 电视新闻会怎么说？
It ain't right having blood on Main Street. How'd that look on TV news?

366
00:32:14,840 --> 00:32:16,260
- 起来  - 我来扶
- Okay, easy.  - Get up.

367
00:32:16,470 --> 00:32:18,250
好的 我扶住他了 我扶好了
Okay, I got him. I got him.

368
00:32:18,350 --> 00:32:20,100
让开
Get out of the way, now.

369
00:32:22,690 --> 00:32:24,000
他是那就餐者的孩子
That's the kid from the diner.

370
00:32:24,100 --> 00:32:27,860
在你和黑人孩子交谈之前 要再三考虑
Now maybe you'll think twice before you talk to colored kids with an audience.

371
00:32:28,020 --> 00:32:31,070
你知道图珀洛方面发来了消息
They're just sending a message from the big boss from Tupelo and you know it!

372
00:32:31,280 --> 00:32:34,400
我知道 克莱顿·汤利 尖头的头目
I know it, yes. Clayton Townley, a chief pointy head.

373
00:32:34,500 --> 00:32:37,490
没错 你怎么知道？
Yeah, that's right. How did you know?

374
00:32:37,700 --> 00:32:39,810
有时也该按局程序 沃德先生
Bureau procedure, Mr. Ward. You ought to try it sometime.

375
00:32:39,910 --> 00:32:41,540
我们会
We did!

376
00:32:41,750 --> 00:32:44,580
我们找过那些孩子开的汽车
We found the car the kids were driving.

377
00:33:24,410 --> 00:33:25,830
早上好
Good morning.

378
00:33:34,970 --> 00:33:36,340
早上好
Good morning.

379
00:34:58,090 --> 00:35:01,800
两个啤酒罐 一个可乐瓶 一个绿色塑料瓶
Two beer cans, a Coca Cola bottle, green plastic bottle,

380
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:05,560
一块烧毁的手表停在十二点四十五 一串钥匙
badly burned wristwatch stopped at 12:45, set of keys.

381
00:35:05,680 --> 00:35:07,210
没有尸体
No bodies.

382
00:35:07,310 --> 00:35:08,770
我要搜索该区
I want the entire area searched.

383
00:35:08,940 --> 00:35:10,090
彻底的搜索
Every inch.

384
00:35:10,190 --> 00:35:11,350
是 长官
Yes, sir.

385
00:35:11,520 --> 00:35:12,710
这是一片大沼泽
It's a big swamp.

386
00:35:12,810 --> 00:35:14,690
伯德先生 彻底搜索
Every inch, Mr. Bird.

387
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:20,950
他们绝对没有离开密西西比州
I guess they never left Mississippi.

388
00:35:22,410 --> 00:35:25,530
他们死了
Yeah, they're dead. They're dead.

389
00:35:25,870 --> 00:35:27,270
伯德先生
Mr. Bird!

390
00:35:27,370 --> 00:35:28,950
什么事？长官
Yes, sir?

391
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:31,670
停车场有电话
There's a telephone back at the truck stop.

392
00:35:31,870 --> 00:35:36,880
去那 打电话 给我叫一百多人来
Get to it, get on it and get me a hundred more men here by morning.

393
00:35:37,050 --> 00:35:38,920
- 一百？ - 一百
- A hundred?  - A hundred.

394
00:35:39,130 --> 00:35:40,700
要局里人吗？长官
What, Bureau people, sir?

395
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:42,340
我不管是否是军队
I don't care if it's the goddamn army!

396
00:35:42,550 --> 00:35:44,500
我只要搜索整个沼泽
I want this entire swamp searched!

397
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:45,800
是 长官
Yes, sir.

398
00:35:48,890 --> 00:35:52,390
沃德先生 别这样 你要发动一场战争
Don't do it, Mr. Ward. You'll just start a war.

399
00:35:53,060 --> 00:35:56,150
我们来之前 就是一场战争了
It was a war long before we got here.

400
00:36:46,280 --> 00:36:47,270
你也是
You too!

401
00:36:47,370 --> 00:36:48,370
醒醒 起来
Wake up! Come on!

402
00:36:53,790 --> 00:36:57,380
离开这里 黑鬼 快走
Get the fuck out of here, nigger! Go on!

403
00:37:36,830 --> 00:37:38,170
长官
Sir?

404
00:37:39,670 --> 00:37:41,200
警长确实不在现场
The sheriff's alibi is solid.

405
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:44,420
那时他与舅子和两个堂弟在玩扑克
He was playing poker with his wife's brother and two cousins.

406
00:37:44,630 --> 00:37:45,740
多久？
The whole time?

407
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:49,680
三个小时 他输了十一块三毛八
No, for three hours. He lost $11.38.

408
00:37:50,300 --> 00:37:51,910
还有件事
There's something else, sir.

409
00:37:52,010 --> 00:37:54,890
汽车旅馆经理找我们的麻烦
We're having a little trouble with the motel manager.

410
00:37:55,100 --> 00:37:56,210
什么麻烦？
What kind of trouble?

411
00:37:56,310 --> 00:37:57,350
他要我们离开
He wants us out.

412
00:37:57,560 --> 00:37:59,420
他说我们妨碍了他的生意
He says we're bad for business.

413
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:01,310
买下来
Buy it.

414
00:38:01,690 --> 00:38:03,190
什么？长官
Sorry, sir?

415
00:38:03,610 --> 00:38:05,150
买下来
Buy it!

416
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:07,110
汽车旅馆
The motel.

417
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:08,850
我能出多高的价？
How high can I go?

418
00:38:08,950 --> 00:38:10,740
不惜一切
Whatever it takes.

419
00:38:33,890 --> 00:38:35,960
今天在密西西比州杰瑟普县
Today in Jessup County, Mississippi,

420
00:38:36,060 --> 00:38:38,810
在本周的暴行中
amidst the violence that has erupted here this week,

421
00:38:39,020 --> 00:38:41,960
政府决定寻找
the eyes of the nation had been firmly fixed on the search

422
00:38:42,060 --> 00:38:44,070
三个失踪的民权工作者
for the three missing civil rights workers.

423
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:45,800
我想这是一个大骗局
Well, I think it's all a big hoax.

424
00:38:45,900 --> 00:38:49,400
要是在沼泽 就会找得到
But if they are in that swamp, then they asked for it.

425
00:38:49,610 --> 00:38:53,240
海军预备队和FBI密探一起
Naval reserves have been brought in to join scores of FBI agents

426
00:38:53,450 --> 00:38:55,450
寻找失踪者
in their search for the missing men.

427
00:38:55,650 --> 00:38:57,600
他们有密谋
I think they planned the whole thing.

428
00:38:57,650 --> 00:39:00,210
他们正在纽约嘲笑我们密西西比人
They're sitting up there in New York laughing at us Mississippi folks.

429
00:39:00,420 --> 00:39:02,400
- 你认为是一个骗局吗？ - 是的
- You think it's a hoax?  - Yeah, I think so.

430
00:39:02,500 --> 00:39:05,420
一个大的骗局 什么也找不到
I think it's a big hoax. They ain't gonna find nothing.

431
00:39:05,590 --> 00:39:10,090
民权领袖对失踪者的下落乐观
Civil rights leaders here are still optimistic as to the men's young whereabouts,

432
00:39:10,260 --> 00:39:14,600
而私下却忧心失踪者是否活着
but privately, there is mounting concern that they will ever be found alive.

433
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:17,350
他们在自找麻烦 我认为他们已经陷入麻烦了
They came down here looking for trouble and I think they found it.

434
00:39:17,560 --> 00:39:21,940
新闻网马雷克·鲍伯比在密西西比州杰瑟普县报道
This is Marek Barlbobi, Network News, Jessup County, Mississippi.

435
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:26,400
我来告诉你 我告诉你他们应该做什么
I'll tell you what. I'll tell you what they ought to be doing.

436
00:39:26,500 --> 00:39:28,610
我认为他们应该去加拿大寻找
They ought to be looking up there in Canada for them boys

437
00:39:28,780 --> 00:39:31,320
而不是在我们这里的沼泽
instead of our swamps around here.

438
00:39:31,530 --> 00:39:34,500
我还会告诉你些别的事情 我想这是NAAC的人
I'll tell you something else too. I think it's a publicity stunt

439
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:37,120
想入非非的表演
dreamed up by these NAACP people.

440
00:39:37,330 --> 00:39:38,520
NAAC的人？
NAACP people?

441
00:39:38,620 --> 00:39:39,910
是的 NAACP（全国有色人种协进会）
Yeah, NAACP.

442
00:39:40,250 --> 00:39:42,000
知道代表什么吗？
I bet you're all wondering what it stands for.

443
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:45,170
代表着黑鬼 鳄鱼 猿 浣熊 负鼠
It stands for niggers, alligators, apes, coons and possums.

444
00:39:45,380 --> 00:39:48,210
你有什么 你有你的NAACP（全国有色人种协进会）
Tell you what you got. You got your NAACP,

445
00:39:48,320 --> 00:39:51,840
你有你的SNCC 你有你的COFO
you got your SNCC, you got your COFO.

446
00:39:52,050 --> 00:39:54,010
你知道所有的混乱是什么吗？
You know what that mess is?

447
00:39:54,220 --> 00:39:57,560
是胡说 你懂吗？
B-U-L-L-S-H-l-T. You got it?

448
00:39:57,770 --> 00:40:00,520
警长 这会是一个联邦案件吗？
Sheriff, will this be a federal case?

449
00:40:02,270 --> 00:40:04,920
有一天 我们不必说
One day there'll come a time when we won't have to say,

450
00:40:05,020 --> 00:40:07,520
“早上好 警长先生”
"Good morning, sir, Mr. Sheriff."

451
00:40:08,110 --> 00:40:12,320
或许那时我们不必说“斯塔基先生”
Maybe there'll come a time when we won't have to say, "Mr. Stuckey".

452
00:40:12,490 --> 00:40:16,910
有一天 我们只说“斯塔基”或“警长”
One day there'll come a time when we just say "Stuckey" or "Sheriff".

453
00:40:17,120 --> 00:40:21,410
有一天 警长甚至不是白人
And one day there'll come a time when the sheriff won't even be a white man.

454
00:40:33,010 --> 00:40:34,340
你好
Hello.

455
00:40:38,140 --> 00:40:40,850
是否能问你一些问题？
I wonder if I could ask you a few questions?

456
00:40:41,060 --> 00:40:44,890
我不认为你会告诉我这是哪种花
I don't suppose you could tell me what kind of flower these are, could you?

457
00:40:45,690 --> 00:40:48,900
我看这里到处都是…
I been seeing them all over the place here and...

458
00:40:49,650 --> 00:40:52,400
从来没见过这么漂亮的植物
I never saw such a darn pretty plant.

459
00:40:53,530 --> 00:40:55,310
叫瓶子草
They're trumpet pitchers.

460
00:40:55,410 --> 00:40:57,200
瓶子草？
Trumpet pitchers?

461
00:40:57,700 --> 00:41:00,370
真的美丽
They're beautiful. They really are.

462
00:41:00,540 --> 00:41:03,960
气味不怎么样 但漂亮
They don't smell so good, but they're pretty.

463
00:41:08,250 --> 00:41:10,400
很高兴与你谈话
It's nice talking to you.

464
00:41:10,500 --> 00:41:12,550
很抱歉打断你们的聚会
Sorry about interrupting your meeting here,

465
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:15,120
可没有人愿与我们交谈
but we can't seem to get anybody to talk to us.

466
00:41:15,220 --> 00:41:17,510
象我妈妈往常说的 他们封嘴了
They just zip up, like my mama used to say.

467
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:20,000
人们不想和你交谈
The reason people don't wanna talk to you

468
00:41:20,100 --> 00:41:22,100
是因为害怕涉及法律
is because they're afraid it'll get back to the law.

469
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:24,090
我们就是法律
We are the law.

470
00:41:24,190 --> 00:41:25,520
你们不是这里的
Not around here, you ain't.

471
00:41:26,350 --> 00:41:29,690
我们来查那些男孩出了什么事
We were sent here to find out what happened to those three boys.

472
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:32,800
他们是来这里帮你们的
They were here to help you.

473
00:41:32,900 --> 00:41:34,900
你们不应该和有色人交谈
It ain't colored floks you should be talking to.

474
00:41:35,570 --> 00:41:37,520
该和谁交谈呢？
Who should we be talking to?

475
00:41:37,620 --> 00:41:39,160
走吧 亚伦
Come on, Aaron.

476
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:43,500
你们应当去警长办公室
You should start with the sheriff's office.

477
00:41:45,710 --> 00:41:47,150
你为什么不害怕？
Why ain't you afraid?

478
00:41:47,250 --> 00:41:48,610
为什么你不害怕？
How come you ain't?

479
00:41:48,710 --> 00:41:49,920
亚伦
Aaron.

480
00:41:51,670 --> 00:41:53,630
亚伦 走吧
Aaron, come on, son.

481
00:42:07,230 --> 00:42:10,610
投球 迅速一击 直球安打
Here's the pitch. Swing and a line-drive base hit!

482
00:42:10,810 --> 00:42:12,610
一人回本垒
Another runner's home!

483
00:42:16,030 --> 00:42:19,280
下个投手是鲍勃·吉布森 他有点紧张
On to the next pitch by the ruffled Bob Gibson. He is upset.

484
00:42:19,450 --> 00:42:21,000
罗恩·亨特一垒打
Ron Hunt singled to center.

485
00:42:21,100 --> 00:42:24,540
希克曼上了三垒 麦兹队赢得第二场
Hickman rounded third and scored the Mets' second run of the game.

486
00:42:24,750 --> 00:42:27,960
亨特在一垒 麦兹队二比一领先
Hunt holds on at first, and the Mets now lead 2 to 1.

487
00:42:28,120 --> 00:42:30,000
下一个上场的是乔·克里斯多夫
And the next one up there will be Joe Christopher,

488
00:42:30,200 --> 00:42:33,090
他三击出局 高飞球被博耶接杀
who struck out and popped out again Boyer.

489
00:42:39,720 --> 00:42:43,830
晚上好 佩尔太太 我是沃德密探 这是安德森密探
Good evening, Mrs. Pell. I'm Agent Ward. This is Agent Anderson.

490
00:42:43,930 --> 00:42:47,810
我们是FBI 你丈夫在家吗？
We're with the FBI. Is your husband home?

491
00:42:48,810 --> 00:42:51,340
我们想和他谈谈
We'd like to have a word with him.

492
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:53,900
进来吧
Y'all come in, then.

493
00:43:00,280 --> 00:43:04,330
克林顿 FBI要问你一些问题
It's the FBI gentlemen, Clinton. They wanna ask you some more questions.

494
00:43:04,990 --> 00:43:07,160
我把你的晚餐放到烤炉去？
You want me to put your dinner in the oven?

495
00:43:09,830 --> 00:43:11,330
你去忙吧
Leave us alone.

496
00:43:12,380 --> 00:43:14,460
介意我坐一坐吗？
Mind if I take a seat?

497
00:43:18,340 --> 00:43:21,010
什么该死的事要在家里打扰我？
What's so goddamn important you gotta bother me at home?

498
00:43:21,220 --> 00:43:24,410
只是想再要你谈谈
Well, I just wanted to run through, once again,

499
00:43:24,510 --> 00:43:26,390
六月二十一日的事
your movements on June 21 st.

500
00:43:26,600 --> 00:43:27,640
六月哪天？
June which?

501
00:43:28,850 --> 00:43:31,250
六月二十一日
June 21st.

502
00:43:31,350 --> 00:43:34,110
现在 我们彼此心知肚明
Now, deputy, we both know what day we're talking about.

503
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:38,690
所以要开诚布公 然后你看你的球赛
So let's be civilized and the sooner you can get back to your ball-game

504
00:43:38,860 --> 00:43:40,570
我们就可以回华盛顿
and we can get back to Washington.

505
00:43:51,120 --> 00:43:53,580
我没打扰你吧
Please, don't let me interrupt you.

506
00:43:54,340 --> 00:43:56,280
一个问题被问十几遍
It's just that when you've heard a question

507
00:43:56,380 --> 00:43:59,670
是有点令人厌烦
asked a dozen times, it gets kind of boring.

508
00:44:00,380 --> 00:44:02,630
是的 我同意
Yeah, I guess so.

509
00:44:09,140 --> 00:44:10,790
你们不一同吃吗？
You don't eat together?

510
00:44:10,890 --> 00:44:12,480
他工作时间不定
He works funny hours.

511
00:44:15,190 --> 00:44:16,310
你觉得奇怪吗？
You think that's odd?

512
00:44:16,900 --> 00:44:18,500
不…
No. No...

513
00:44:19,070 --> 00:44:21,190
我自己就这样
I work funny hours myself.

514
00:44:22,990 --> 00:44:26,030
我饿了 就吃 他饿了 他就吃
I eat when I'm hungry, he eats when he can.

515
00:44:26,240 --> 00:44:29,580
- 要来点什么吗？ - 不 谢谢
- Can I get you something?  - No, no, thanks.

516
00:44:29,790 --> 00:44:33,000
这房子不错 在这里生活多久了？
This is a nice house. How long have you lived here?

517
00:44:33,210 --> 00:44:35,040
我在这里出生
I was born here.

518
00:44:35,250 --> 00:44:38,840
很久以前我父亲玩扑克游戏输掉了这房子
But my father lost the house in a poker game one night a long time ago.

519
00:44:40,840 --> 00:44:43,590
从那以后我们一直支付房租
We've been paying rent ever since.

520
00:44:46,680 --> 00:44:48,550
那是一种邪恶的游戏
It's a wicked game.

521
