Good luck.

862
01:11:45,380 --> 01:11:48,420
你们要指控我 就知道去哪里查我
You get enough to indict me, you know where to find me.

863
01:11:52,300 --> 01:11:54,220
- 怎么样？ - 没事
- How'd it go?  - Fine. It went just fine.

864
01:11:54,390 --> 01:11:56,760
别担心那些该死的事
Don't you worry about a goddamn thing.

865
01:11:58,150 --> 01:11:59,770
你会被指控吗？
Are you gonna be indicted?

866
01:11:59,980 --> 01:12:02,480
FBI有指控警长办公室的证据吗？
Does the FBI have evidence that the Sheriff's office is invovled?

867
01:12:02,690 --> 01:12:04,880
你与他们合作吗？
Are you cooperating in this investigation?

868
01:12:04,980 --> 01:12:07,000
我们一惯合作
We're cooperating just like we have all along.

869
01:12:07,050 --> 01:12:08,800
毫无证据可言
They have no damn evidence either. It's all circumstancial.

870
01:12:08,850 --> 01:12:13,570
先生 请不要拍摄
Sir, could you not do that, please? Sir, do not do that, please!

871
01:12:15,500 --> 01:12:17,280
已经告诉你了 现在 给我滚开
Don't you understand? Now, get the fuck out of here!

872
01:12:20,000 --> 01:12:21,850
要告诉你两千次吗？
We have to tell you two thousand times?

873
01:12:21,900 --> 01:12:24,250
从哪来滚哪去
Now get out of here and go back where you belong!

874
01:12:24,590 --> 01:12:26,250
在我面前消失
Get out of my face, boy!

875
01:12:26,800 --> 01:12:29,210
滚开 别打扰我们
Get on out and leave us alone!

876
01:12:29,400 --> 01:12:30,600
别打扰我们
Leave us alone!

877
01:12:31,180 --> 01:12:34,140
从哪来滚哪去 你找揍呀
Go on home where you belong! Boy, you're gonna get hurt now.

878
01:12:36,560 --> 01:12:39,850
沃德先生 此事我们勉强能接受
Mr. Ward, this is getting to be just about as much as we can take.

879
01:12:40,060 --> 01:12:41,550
可我无法表达更强的怨言
I cannot register my complaints more strongly.

880
01:12:41,600 --> 01:12:42,710
现在无法 先生
Not now, sir.

881
01:12:42,810 --> 01:12:43,810
现在 你只有一分钟
Now, you just a minute.

882
01:12:44,860 --> 01:12:47,820
我对公众追逐我的警长处很不满意
I resent your public pursuit of my Sheriff's department.

883
01:12:48,030 --> 01:12:51,530
你在竭尽所能将他们牵涉进这些失踪案
You have made every effort to implicate them in these disappearances.

884
01:12:51,740 --> 01:12:54,700
含沙射影并不能证明
But your goddamn slimey innuendos are not evidence

885
01:12:54,750 --> 01:12:56,450
他们涉及任何罪行
that they were any way connected with any crime.

886
01:12:56,620 --> 01:12:59,410
我们正在设法发掘真相 但有阻碍
We're just trying to get to the truth. It's frustrating for us too!

887
01:12:59,620 --> 01:13:02,960
任何傻瓜可以出来指控 沃德 但那不是证据
Anyone jackass can point a finger, Ward. Now, that ain't evidence.

888
01:13:03,120 --> 01:13:07,130
在这里 旧棉花间苗机的使用者们还会蠢得去相信民主
Down here, us old cotton-choppers are still stupid enough to believe in democracy.

889
01:13:07,340 --> 01:13:10,670
我们要懂得按法律行使权利
And you can rest assured, sir, we know our rights under the law!

890
01:13:10,880 --> 01:13:13,760
你知道就好 我用一台棉花间苗机来打赌
You know something all right. I'll bet a cotton-chopping dollar on that.

891
01:13:14,010 --> 01:13:17,400
你知道吗 安德森 你越来越咄咄逼人
You know what, Anderson? You're starting to get so far up my nose,

892
01:13:17,450 --> 01:13:19,680
我开始觉得你在威胁我
I'm beginning to feel your boots on my chin.

893
01:13:20,180 --> 01:13:23,100
我再次告诉你
And I'm telling you one more time, Mr. apple-red,

894
01:13:23,200 --> 01:13:25,500
几个披着床单的疯子
a couple of crazies dressed in bed sheets

895
01:13:25,550 --> 01:13:28,000
在乡下跳舞来吓唬黑人
dancing around the countryside scaring Negroes

896
01:13:28,050 --> 01:13:30,800
不是整个密西西比州的错
is not the goddamn fault of the entire state of Mississippi!

897
01:13:30,900 --> 01:13:33,820
我告诉你 提尔曼 有三个孩子死亡
I'm telling you, Tilman, there are three dead kids out there somewhere,

898
01:13:34,030 --> 01:13:36,680
很多人害怕 这都是因为你的警长处
and a lot of scared people because of your goddamn Sheriff's department.

899
01:13:36,780 --> 01:13:38,530
大家要相互体谅
So you better get used to having us around.

900
01:13:38,740 --> 01:13:42,160
也体谅我威胁你
And you better get used to my boots on your chin too.

901
01:13:42,500 --> 01:13:44,580
你们最好放弃
You people better back off!

902
01:13:45,960 --> 01:13:48,790
该死的FBI 自以为是
Goddamn FBI! Just who on hell do they think they are?

903
01:13:49,000 --> 01:13:50,530
敢来我的地盘…
Coming down on my part of the goddamn country harassing...

904
01:13:50,630 --> 01:13:51,840
市长先生 你有要说的吗？
Do you have a statement, Mr. Mayor?

905
01:13:52,050 --> 01:13:53,800
该死的我当然有
You got goddamn right I got a statement!

906
01:13:54,010 --> 01:13:56,220
安德森先生 刚才
For a moment there, Mr. Anderson,

907
01:13:57,010 --> 01:14:00,460
我们彼此立场相同
it sounded like we were both on the same side.

908
01:14:28,000 --> 01:14:29,280
宝贝 你好吗？
Are you all right, honey?

909
01:14:29,380 --> 01:14:30,540
我很好
Yeah, I'm fine.

910
01:14:30,710 --> 01:14:32,150
有什么就叫我
Let me know if you need anything.

911
01:14:32,250 --> 01:14:34,130
谢谢 我会的
Thanks, I will.

912
01:15:58,800 --> 01:16:00,300
妈妈 快来
Mama, Mama, come quick!

913
01:16:16,980 --> 01:16:19,890
没有他的踪迹 他离开很久了
There's no sign of him, sir. He's long gone.

914
01:16:19,990 --> 01:16:23,720
他母亲住在街对面 她可能不会开门
His mother, she lives across the street. She won't talk to us. Won't even answer the door.

915
01:16:23,820 --> 01:16:27,290
我想整个区一定有人看见了
I want the whole area covered. Someone must have seen something.

916
01:16:27,490 --> 01:16:28,730
他们不会说 先生
They won't talk to us, sir.

917
01:16:28,830 --> 01:16:33,000
伯德先生 走吧 如果他们不说 就摆脱不了
Get going, Mr. Bird. If they won't talk to us, shake it out of them.

918
01:16:36,000 --> 01:16:38,630
好吧 我们走 去每个住宅 快点
All right, let's go. Every house. Come on.

919
01:16:45,260 --> 01:16:46,680
怎么？
What?

920
01:16:47,100 --> 01:16:51,390
这些白人会四处销毁痕迹
Sending all these white guys chasing around these dog tracks with their little notebooks

921
01:16:51,600 --> 01:16:53,380
你将一无所获
is gonna get you nowhere.

922
01:16:53,480 --> 01:16:56,270
你能做什么？
Okay. What would you do?

923
01:17:01,450 --> 01:17:02,860
可以害怕
It's okay to be afraid.

924
01:17:11,160 --> 01:17:12,910
快点 威利
Go on, Willie.

925
01:17:13,750 --> 01:17:15,540
告诉他们
Tell them what you saw.

926
01:17:49,370 --> 01:17:51,370
被告站起来
The defendants will rise.

927
01:17:55,040 --> 01:17:58,580
在这个国家 一个人的家就是他的避难所
In this country, a man's home is his castle.

928
01:17:59,500 --> 01:18:04,090
那是这个社会生存的一个原则
That is one of the principles by which this community survives.

929
01:18:04,260 --> 01:18:07,300
你们已经破坏了这个原则
You men have done violence to that principle.

930
01:18:07,510 --> 01:18:11,000
但我要你们知道 法庭了解
But I want you to know that the court understands

931
01:18:11,100 --> 01:18:12,720
你们已经犯的罪
that the crimes that you have comitted

932
01:18:12,930 --> 01:18:14,730
至少在某种程度上
have been, to some extent at least,

933
01:18:15,390 --> 01:18:18,670
是受外来影响
brought about by outside influences.

934
01:18:27,740 --> 01:18:34,660
外人已经进入杰瑟普县 他们是道德卑贱的人
Outsiders have come into Jessup County and they've been people of low morality.

935
01:18:35,540 --> 01:18:37,960
不洁净的人
And unhygienic.

936
01:18:38,330 --> 01:18:41,590
他们的存在激怒了许多人
And their presence here has provoked a lot of people.

937
01:18:44,300 --> 01:18:50,370
因此法庭了解 没有宽恕他们 请注意
So the court understands, without condoning them, mind you,

938
01:18:50,470 --> 01:18:55,140
你们已经承认有罪的 至少在某种程度上
that the crimes to which you men have pled guilty were, to some extent at least,

939
01:18:56,020 --> 01:18:59,770
是这些外来影响引起的
provoked by these outside influences.

940
01:19:01,480 --> 01:19:04,980
鉴于所有一切 我将从轻处罚你们
So with all this, I'm gonna make your punishment light.

941
01:19:06,990 --> 01:19:10,320
我打算判你们每人五年监禁
I'm gonna sentence you each to five years imprisonment.

942
01:19:14,660 --> 01:19:18,400
但我要延缓判决
But I'm gonna suspend these sentences.

943
01:19:51,910 --> 01:19:54,030
你们不能进去 先生
You can't go in there, sir.

944
01:19:54,700 --> 01:19:56,850
FBI 让我们进去
FBI. Let us through.

945
01:19:56,950 --> 01:19:59,080
抱歉 你们不能进去
I'm sorry, sir. You can't go in there.

946
01:20:04,540 --> 01:20:06,130
警长
Sheriff!

947
01:20:09,840 --> 01:20:12,430
你们真的在进行一些事
You started something this time.

948
01:20:12,640 --> 01:20:15,050
车让开 我要进去和他们谈
Can you move these cars? I wanna go in there and talk to them.

949
01:20:15,220 --> 01:20:16,790
你去 只要你能去
No, you're gone as far as you're gonna go.

950
01:20:16,890 --> 01:20:18,720
我们能处理
This ain't nothing we can't handle.

951
01:20:18,930 --> 01:20:21,590
只是一些疯狂的有色人挖开了自己的屁眼
Just a bunch of crazy coloreds tearing up their own assholes.

952
01:20:21,690 --> 01:20:23,440
地方问题
Local problem.

953
01:20:39,580 --> 01:20:41,410
沃德先生 瞧那火
Look at those flames, Mr. Ward.

954
01:20:42,540 --> 01:20:44,830
那就是他们要你来的原因 是吗？
That's why they sent you down here, wasn't it?

955
01:20:45,040 --> 01:20:47,630
你知道的 总之发生了
It would've happened anyway and you know it.

956
01:20:49,210 --> 01:20:53,010
我要是黑人 我可能会用同样的方式
You know, if I was a Negro, I'd probably think the same way they do.

957
01:20:53,640 --> 01:20:54,700
你要是黑人
If you were a Negro,

958
01:20:54,800 --> 01:20:58,010
没人会在乎你的想法
nobody would give a damn what you thought.

959
01:21:54,650 --> 01:21:56,700
亚伦 亚伦 起来
Aaron, Aaron, Aaron, get up!

960
01:21:56,910 --> 01:21:59,280
带你妈妈 奶奶和孩子们从后门出去 听到了吗？
Take your mama, you grand-mama and the children out the back door. You hear?

961
01:21:59,490 --> 01:22:03,700
离开后 就快走 明白吗？快走 儿子
When you hit the road, keep going. You understand? Keep going, son.

962
01:22:05,370 --> 01:22:08,210
内森 快起来 内森 快起来 内森
Nathan! Come on, Nathan! Get up! Get up, Nathan, now!

963
01:22:08,790 --> 01:22:10,400
快起来 下床
Come on! Get out the bed!

964
01:22:10,500 --> 01:22:12,050
怎么了？
What's happening?

965
01:22:13,130 --> 01:22:16,510
起来 妈妈 我们快走
Come on, Mama! Let's go! Come on, Mama!

966
01:22:18,180 --> 01:22:19,720
你们快走
Come on, y'all!

967
01:22:19,930 --> 01:22:21,290
快起来 孩子
Get up, child.

968
01:22:21,390 --> 01:22:22,720
快走 奶奶
Come on, Grandma!

969
01:22:23,180 --> 01:22:24,520
我们走
Let's go!

970
01:22:31,720 --> 01:22:39,430
♫ 你们都辛劳 ♫
♪ All ye who labour ♪

971
01:22:39,700 --> 01:22:41,120
是谁？
Who's there?

972
01:22:41,660 --> 01:22:45,040
谁在那 出来 听到吗？
If you're in there, come on out. You hear?

973
01:22:45,790 --> 01:22:48,460
我别无选择
I ain't taking this shit no more!

974
01:23:02,790 --> 01:23:11,160
♫ 肩负你的重任 ♫
♪ Bring him your burdens ♪

975
01:23:12,760 --> 01:23:18,590
♫ 并非他的宠爱 ♫
♪ Seek not his favour ♪

976
01:23:19,350 --> 01:23:27,440
♫ 向他… 向他倾诉你的痛苦 ♫
♪ Tell... tell him your sorrows ♪

977
01:23:28,940 --> 01:23:39,360
♫ 向… 他… 倾诉 ♫
♪ In... him... confide ♪

978
01:23:41,950 --> 01:23:45,870
♫ 他满足 ♫
♪ He satisfies ♪

979
01:23:46,710 --> 01:23:50,620
♫ 他满足 ♫
♪ He satisfies ♪

980
01:23:53,190 --> 01:23:55,110
还好吧 爸爸
You'll be okay, Papa.

981
01:23:55,570 --> 01:23:57,570
妈妈和女孩们都好
Mama and the girls are fine.

982
01:23:57,780 --> 01:23:59,490
你的头受伤了
They just cracked your head some.

983
01:23:59,700 --> 01:24:03,370
要保持呼吸 你别死
You just keep on breathing. Don't you go dying on me now.

984
01:24:03,620 --> 01:24:05,370
听到吗？
You hear me?

985
01:24:06,580 --> 01:24:08,540
你会没事的
You're gonna be just fine.

986
01:24:35,980 --> 01:24:38,150
你看 母牛不会跑
You know, cows won't run away.

987
01:24:38,280 --> 01:24:40,820
没人知道为什么 我想它们只是愚蠢
No one knows why. They're just stupid, I guess.

988
01:24:41,320 --> 01:24:46,200
它们站那里直到吃饱喝足
They just stand there until their bellies swell up and they pop.

989
01:24:46,530 --> 01:24:48,950
他们有亲戚在底特律
They have relatives in Detroit.

990
01:24:49,950 --> 01:24:51,560
他们去哪里？
Are they gonna go?

991
01:24:51,660 --> 01:24:53,670
我没给他们任何选择
I didn't give them any choice.

992
01:24:55,170 --> 01:24:57,210
至少我们知道谁干的
At least, we know who did this.

993
01:24:58,170 --> 01:24:59,610
是我们
We did.

994
01:24:59,710 --> 01:25:01,410
别烦躁 会有进展
Don't fret. It's progress.

995
01:25:01,510 --> 01:25:04,930
二十年前他们对偷西瓜的都要吊死
Twenty years ago, they'd strung them up for stealing watermelons.

996
01:25:05,680 --> 01:25:10,100
我不明白 安德森先生 根本没有这种事
I don't understand you, Mr. Anderson. Not at all.

997
01:25:10,560 --> 01:25:13,020
我们坦诚一点吧
Let's get something straight, all right?

998
01:25:13,230 --> 01:25:17,500
此事情经新闻报道就被弄糟了
This whole thing was fucked up the moment we turned it into a show for the newsmen.

999
01:25:17,600 --> 01:25:20,300
三个孩子失踪就是新闻
The moment these three kids disappeared, it was news.

1000
01:25:20,360 --> 01:25:24,450
三个民权工作者失踪就是新闻
The moment the three civil rights workers disappeared, it was news.

1001
01:25:24,660 --> 01:25:27,780
他们只是孩子 至今下落不明
To me they're just kids. They're still missing.

1002
01:25:27,990 --> 01:25:32,700
佩尔说跟他妻子一起五十分钟
What's missing is the 50 minutes Pell said he was with his wife.

1003
01:25:36,250 --> 01:25:37,960
行
Okay.

1004
01:25:54,100 --> 01:25:55,730
我爱密西西比州
I love Mississippi.

1005
01:26:08,100 --> 01:26:09,300
他们…
They...

1006
01:26:09,740 --> 01:26:11,580
他们不喜欢密西西比州
They hate Mississippi.

1007
01:26:12,830 --> 01:26:15,160
他们恨我们是因为我们做了
They hate us, because we present

1008
01:26:15,370 --> 01:26:20,090
种族隔离的辉煌典范
a shining example of successful segregation.

1009
01:26:20,250 --> 01:26:24,760
这些北方学生 与他们的无神论者 共产主义上司
These northern students, with their atheist, Communist bosses,

1010
01:26:24,920 --> 01:26:28,800
今年夏天进入我们社区妄图摧毁这个典范
that have come into our community this summer with the wish to destroy it,

1011
01:26:29,010 --> 01:26:33,180
本周已采取了可怕的打击
this week, have taken a terrible blow.

1012
01:26:33,430 --> 01:26:37,190
他们的企图破灭了
This week, their cause has been crippled.

1013
01:26:37,400 --> 01:26:40,800
本周 这些联邦警察在窥探我们的生活
This week, all of these federal policemen you see out here

1014
01:26:40,850 --> 01:26:44,000
侵犯我们公民的自由
prying into our lives violating our civil beliefs

1015
01:26:44,100 --> 01:26:47,110
据了解 他们无力反对我们
have learned that they are powerless against us,

1016
01:26:47,320 --> 01:26:51,450
每个盎格鲁撒克逊基督徒
if every single Anglo-Saxon Christian one of us

1017
01:26:51,620 --> 01:26:52,780
与我们站在一起
stands together!

1018
01:26:58,170 --> 01:26:59,500
本周…
This week...

1019
01:27:00,630 --> 01:27:03,420
- 沃德？ - 有客人
- Mr. Ward?  - We got company, sir.

1020
01:27:04,260 --> 01:27:06,630
你为何在此？这是政治性集会
You got no right to be here. This is a political meeting.

1021
01:27:06,800 --> 01:27:08,450
我并没感到这种气氛 副警长
Doesn't smell that way to me, Deputy.

1022
01:27:08,550 --> 01:27:10,470
这是政治性集会 胡佛男孩
It's a goddamn political meeting, Hoover boy!

1023
01:27:11,000 --> 01:27:16,560
是象政治性集会 但气氛更象三K党
Oh, it looks like a political meeting, but smells more like Klan to me.

1024
01:27:16,810 --> 01:27:19,980
不管有没有穿万圣节服装
With or without the Halloween costumes.

1025
01:27:20,810 --> 01:27:22,310
先生们
Gentlemen.

1026
01:27:22,480 --> 01:27:26,190
在密西西比州法庭 已经提醒他们
In the courts of Mississippi, they have been reminded

1027
01:27:26,400 --> 01:27:32,120
他们不能凭借武力将我们社区变成他们社区的摹本
that they cannot by force turn our communities into relicas of their communities.

1028
01:27:32,330 --> 01:27:36,660
社区里黑人闹事没受限制 没受处罚
Communities in which Negroes run riot, unrestrained and unpunished

1029
01:27:36,870 --> 01:27:39,210
今年夏天在哈莱姆街道
as they do this summer in the streets of Harlem,

1030
01:27:39,420 --> 01:27:41,080
奥克兰街道
